headline: Carnival (CCL) Is Up 8.8% After Record 2025 Results And Dividend Return - What's Changed
summary: Carnival Corporation & plc has reported record full-year 2025 results, with revenue rising to US$26.62 billion and net income reaching US$2.76 billion, and has reinstated a quarterly dividend of US$0.15 per share for payment in February 2026. Alongside these results, Carnival has proposed unifying its dual-listed structure into a single NYSE-listed Bermuda-incorporated company, aiming to simplify governance while continuing to strengthen its balance sheet and credit profile.
